itive wonders.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nBaby you don’t even know I’m falling apartIn your fun and games, You’ve stolen my heart.\n\n- Ahmed\n|\nThe greater the spirit, the more one is alone.\n\n- Suzy\n|\nAll I wanted was for my mom to say, 'I love you, and I'm here for you.' I never got that.\n\n- Kendra\n|\nDo something that surprises yourself cause if you don't surprise yourself, you're not going to surprise anybody else.\n\n- Logan\n|\nThe utility of adversity is to draw inspiration, wisdom and strength from it.\n\n- Ifeanyi\n|\nOnly one thing remained reachable, close and secure amid all losses: language. Yes, language. In spite of everything, it remained secure against loss.\n\n- Paul\n|\nYour future is a finished work. God created your future; your thoughts guide you to locate it and your passion takes you there. However, it’s your attitude that makes you stay!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Daily Drive 365\n|\nGod be with you.''Thanks, but I think, in battle, I prefer Satan’s company.\n\n- Robert Thier, The Robber Knight's Love\n|\nThere will be days that I don't think we'll know how to survive. But we will, because we have each other.\n\n- Colleen Hoover, Hopeless\n|\nWhere there's love, gossip won't strive or thrive.\n\n- Kemi\n|\nIt would be a decision she made with her will, rather than with her heart, and she would pay a price for it.\n\n- Aditi\n|\nI don’t think they can deal with someone being complex and contradictory; it’s not acceptable, you have to be a cartoon, a stereotype.\n\n- Shirley\n|\nAngels do not toil, but let their good works grow out of them.\n\n- Nathaniel Hawthorne, The House of the Seven Gables\n|\nIn the oddity or maybe the miracle of life, the roots of something new frequently lie in the decaying husks of something old.\n\n- Craig\n|\nAs long as grace abounds, I will work with all my strength.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nNecessity, they say, is the mother of invention, but fear, too, is 